{This is the Carlsbad structure with colours reversed. In the Two Knights Variation, this structure appears when there is a piece exchange on d5 and Black recaptures with the c6-pawn. In our variation, you will usually get this structure due to the exchange of the light-squared bishops. This exchange is favourable for Black since White's attacking potential is highly reduced. On the other hand, it's pretty easy for Black to execute his minority attack on the queenside.}  *

