{The following model game shows that Black can even retreat the bishop on c7 in this structure. The idea is to overprotect the vulnerable b6-pawn. The position of interest arises after Black's 18...Bc7.} 1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. d3 Qc7 4. exd5 cxd5 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 e6 7. a3 dxc4 8. dxc4 a6 9. g3 Bd6 10. Bg2 b6 11. O-O Bb7 12. Be3 Nbd7 13. Qe2 O-O 14. Rfd1 Rfd8 15. Rac1 Rac8 16. b4 h6 17. h3 Qb8 18. Rc2 Bc7 {The idea of this move is to overprotect the b6-pawn. By doing so, Black frees the d7-knight. Therefore, in such positions, we can often consider the maneuver ...Nd7-f8-g6. Of course, whenever White retreats the f3-knight we go for ...Ne5.} ({There is nothing wrong with the alternative} 18... Be7 {The game might continue with} 19. Rcd2 Qa8 20. Kh2 Bc6 $13 {when Black's position remains perfectly sound.}) 19. Ne1 {Black is always glad to see this move. Besides exchanging the light-squared bishops, he will also put a knight on e5.} ({If White goes for a waiting strategy, Black is ready to follow with ...Qa8 and ...Nf8. For instance, after} 19. Rcd2 Qa8 20. Kh2 Nf8 $13 {Black is doing completely fine. The possibility of ...Nf8-g6 is one of the main points behind ...Bc7. Note that after putting the knight on g6, Black can sometimes consider expanding with ...e6-e5-e4 followed by ...Ne5. Of course, all these ideas should be based on precise calculation.}) 19... Ne5 20. Bxb7 Qxb7 21. Rxd8+ Rxd8 $13 {Black does not have problems. The vulnerability of the white king, as well as the weakened c4-pawn, make Black's position practically easier.} 22. Rd2 Rxd2 23. Bxd2 Qc6 24. b5 axb5 25. cxb5 Qc4 26. a4 Qb3 (26... Nfd7 $15) 27. Nf3 Nxf3+ 28. Qxf3 Be5 29. Kg2 Bxc3 30. Bxc3 Nd5 31. Be5 Qxa4 32. Qd3 Qb4 33. Bd4 Qd6 34. Qc4 Qd7 35. Kg1 Qd8 36. h4 f6 37. Qc6 Kf7 38. Bb2 h5 39. Bd4 Qe8 40. Qb7+ Qe7 41. Qc6 Qd8 42. Qb7+ Qe7 43. Qc6 Qc7 44. Qa8 Qc1+ 45. Kg2 Qc4 46. Qb7+ Kg6 47. Be3 Qe4+ 48. Kg1 Kf5 49. Qxg7 Nxe3 50. Qh7+ Ke5 51. Qc7+ Kf5 52. Qh7+ Ke5 53. Qc7+ Kd4 54. Qxb6+ Kc4 55. fxe3 Qb1+ 56. Kh2 Qc2+ 57. Kh3 Qf5+ 58. Kg2 Qc2+ 59. Kf3 Qf5+ 60. Ke2 Qc2+ 61. Ke1 Qb1+ 62. Kf2 Qf5+ 63. Kg1 Qb1+ 64. Kh2 Qc2+ 65. Kh3 Qf5+ 66. g4 hxg4+ 67. Kh2 Qf2+ 68. Kh1 Qf1+ 69. Kh2 Qf2+ 70. Kh1 g3 71. Qxe6+ Kd3 72. Qb3+ Ke4 73. Qc4+ Kf3 74. Qf4+ Ke2 75. Qc4+ Kd2 76. Qd4+ Ke2 77. Qb2+ Kxe3 78. Qc3+ Ke4 79. Qc4+ Kf5 80. Qd5+ Kg4 81. Qe6+ Kxh4 82. Qe4+ Kg5 83. Qd5+ f5 84. Qg2 Qe1+ 85. Qg1 Qe4+ 86. Qg2 Qb1+ 87. Qg1 Qe4+ 88. Qg2 Qh4+ 89. Kg1 Qd4+ 90. Kh1 Kh4 91. Qf3 Qa1+ 92. Kg2 Qb2+ 93. Kg1 Qd4+ 94. Kg2 Qd2+ 95. Kf1 Qc1+ 96. Kg2 Qb2+ 97. Kg1 1-0

