{This is the main strucure that we will be getting in the Exchange Variation. This is the so-called Carlsbad structure with colours reversed. White's main idea is to play on the kingside by making use of the semi-open e-file. In these positions, White also tries to make use of the important e5-square. On the other hand, Black's main strategic goal is to induce queenside weaknesses by employing the so-called minority attack based on ...b7-b5-b4. An additional idea is the advance ...e6-e5 which will take us to a very interesting version of IQP.}  *

