{This structure usually arises when in the normal Carlsbad structure (Structure 1) the white e5-knight has been exchanged. It's important to understand that this structure is statically favourable for Black. There are three reasons for this evaluation: 1) The possibility of playing on the c-file 2) The minority attack based on the advance ...b7-b5-b4 3) The potential vulnerability of the e5-pawn White's chances, therefore, are connected with a kingside attack in the middlegame. As you will see in the model games, however, Black has more than enough defensive resources. This is the perfect position you want to get when playing for a win.}  *

