{ [#]Black has done everything right, doubling rooks on the e-file and controlling the blocking square on d4. But he still needs a plan to increase his pressure. } 23... g5 $1 { A multi-purpose move, continuing the fight for the d4-square and aiming at clearing the f-file to create threats against f2. } 24. h3 ( 24. Rxd5 Re2 $17 ) 24... h5 25. Nh2 $6 { This is too passive to be good. } ( 25. Nd4 $6 { is premature: } 25... Nxd4 26. cxd4 ( 26. Rxd4 Re2 $17 ) 26... g4 27. h4 ( { White needs to keep the kingside blocked as after } 27. hxg4 hxg4 { [%cal Gg8g7, Ge8h8] followed by ...Kg7 and ...Rh8 Black's attack would be unstoppable. } ) 27... Re2 $1 28. Rxe2 Qf3+ 29. Kg1 Rxe2 30. Qf1 Rxb2 $19 ) ( { A neutral move such as } 25. Rc1 { fails to keep troubles away: } 25... g4 26. Nd4 Nxd4 $17 27. Rxd4 $2 Re1 $1 28. Qxe1 Qf3+ 29. Kg1 Rxe1+ 30. Rxe1 gxh3 $19 ) ( { The only surviving chance was } 25. Kg1 $1 { removing the king from the exposed square. } 25... g4 26. Nd4 Nxd4 27. Rxd4 Rxd4 ( { The point is that } 27... Re2 { runs into } 28. Rf4 $14 ) 28. Qxd4 Qxd4 29. cxd4 Re2 30. Rc1 { with every chance to hold the rook ending. } ) 25... g4 26. hxg4 hxg4 27. Kg1 ( 27. Nxg4 Qg5 28. Nh2 Re1 $1 { wins material as the rooks are hanging. The only way to limit the damage is } 29. Qg4 Qxg4 30. Nxg4 Rxa1 31. Nf6+ Kf8 32. Nxe8 Kxe8 33. Rxd5 $17 ) 27... d4 $19 28. Nxg4 Qg5 29. Rd3 Rxg4 30. cxd4 Nxg3 0-1[Event "BCF-ch"]
