{ [#]White tried to reduce Black's pressure with } 28. Rd4 { Was this a good idea? ***Not quite as the queen and bishop are exposed: } 28... Nh4 $1 29. Qg3 ( 29. Qe2 Qg6 { offers Black a winning attack: } 30. g4 ( 30. Qf1 Nf3+ ) ( 30. g3 Rxe3 31. fxe3 Qxg3+ 32. Kh1 Qxh3+ 33. Qh2 Qf3+ 34. Kg1 Re6 ) 30... Rxd4 31. cxd4 Qe4 $19 ) ( 29. Qh5 R8e5 { forces the queen back anyway, gaining an attacking tempo for Black. } ) 29... Qxg3 30. fxg3 Rxe3 31. gxh4 Rxc3 32. Rad1 ( 32. Rxd5 Re2 $17 { followed by ...Rcc2 is hopeless. } ) 32... Re2 33. h5 Rg3 { and Black won. } 34. Kf1 Rgxg2 35. Rxd5 Ref2+ 36. Ke1 Rxa2 37. Rd8+ Kh7 38. Kf1 Raf2+ 39. Ke1 Rb2 40. Kf1 Rh2 41. Kg1 Rxh3 42. R8d7 Rg3+ 43. Kh1 Rbxb3 44. Rxf7 Rg4 45. Rd8 Rh3# 0-1[Event "?"]
