{ Let's get back to our basic IQP position. White's attempt to put pressure on the e7-pawn is completely ineffective. In this game, he tried } 12. Bg5 Bb7 13. Rfe1 $6 { After this dubious move, Black has an obvious advantage. White's problem is that Black can just take the d5-pawn for free. } ( { More to the point would have been } 13. Bxf6 { As we know, however, the structure arising after } 13... exf6 { is quite favourable for Black. The game might continue } 14. Rfe1 Qd6 15. Qb3 Rfd8 { The d5-pawn is under strong pressure and will be lost soon. White has nothing better than making natural moves such as } 16. h3 Rac8 { Black has all the necessary time to mobilize all his forces. } ( { A blunder would be } 16... Bxd5 $4 { since after } 17. Nxd5 Qxd5 18. Re8+ $18 { White is winning. } ) 17. Rac1 Qb8 $15 { [%cal Gg7f8,Gg8g7] Black is very well coordinated. After useful moves such as ...Bf8 and ...Kg7, he can consider regaining the pawn with ...Qd6 or .. .Qa8. Black is obviously slightly better in this position. } ) 13... Nxd5 { Taking the pawn is possible due to the exposed position of the white queen. } 14. Qe2 { This passive move allows Black to further consolidate his advantage. } ( { The attempt to increase the pressure on e7 by means of } 14. Nxd5 Bxd5 15. Qb4 { can be easily neutralized with } 15... f6 16. Bf4 Rf7 $15 { [%cal Gg7f8,Ge7e6] with .. .e7-e6 and ...Bf8 to follow. Black has a stable advantage due to his better structure and powerful bishops. } ) 14... Re8 15. Rac1 Rc8 { White should already reckon with ...Nxc3, creating a backward pawn on c3. In the game, after } 16. Bd2 { Black played the precise } 16... Nxc3 17. bxc3 e5 $1 { A very nice way of exploiting the opposition along the e-file. White cannot take with the knight in view of ...f7-f6. He has nothing better than going for the line } 18. Be3 exd4 19. cxd4 Qd5 $17 { when Black enjoys full domination. White is quite helpless against Black's play on the light squares. } 20. Qb2 Qh5 21. Rxc8 Rxc8 22. Ne5 Bd5 23. Qb5 Rd8 24. Nc6 Bxc6 25. Qxc6 Qa5 26. Qc4 0-1[Event "?"]
