{ [#] Finally, we will take a look at some positions with doubled pawns on the f-file. We have already examined this position in the theoretical part. In general, all these positions with doubled pawns on the f-file tend to be quite favourable for Black. Remember that Black is not in a hurry to quickly regain the pawn. White does not have constructive ideas anyway. At this point, Black played } 11... a5 { By creating the threat of ...a5-a4, Black wants to provoke the advance a2-a4. Afterward, we can make use of the b4-square. } 12. a4 Qd6 { [%cal Gf8d8,Gg7f8,Gd6b4] A key move in Black's strategy. His plan includes the moves ...Rd8 followed by ...Bf8, and ...Qb4. The game went } 13. O-O Rd8 14. Rfe1 Bf8 15. h3 Qb4 { This was Black's entire idea. Of course, White cannot allow the exchange of the queens. The white queen is now forced to retreat to a passive square. } 16. Qa2 Bf5 { Another precise move. Black has two ideas of improving the position - the maneuver ...Bc2-b3, and ...Rac8 followed by ... Nc4. } 17. Bd1 { [%cal Gd1b3] The most sensible move. White intends to transfer the bishop to b3. The following couple of moves are quite logical - } 17... Bd3 18. Bb3 Rac8 { Black is now ready to exchange the light-squared bishops with ... Bc4 on the next move. } 19. Ne4 { It's understandable that White is desperately looking for some activity. As often happens in such structures, however, the white knights lack good squares in the centre. } ( { Another attempt to complicate matters would have been } 19. d6 { Even in this case, however, Black keeps the control after } 19... Bc4 20. Bxc4 Nxc4 21. b3 Nb6 22. Ne4 Nd5 $15 { [%cal Gf8d6] when the d6-pawn is going to be lost. Black keeps a slight edge. } ) 19... f5 20. Nc3 Bc4 $15 { After the exchange of the bishops, White will not be able to hold the material advantage. In the resulting position, Black will be slightly better in view of his favourable pawn structure. } 21. Bxc4 Qxc4 22. Qxc4 Rxc4 23. Nb5 Rxa4 24. Rxa4 Nxa4 25. d6 Nxb2 26. Re7 Bxe7 27. dxe7 Re8 28. d5 Rxe7 29. d6 Rd7 30. Ne5 Rd8 0-1[Event "?"]
