{In this chapter, we shall take a look at some rare alternatives for White on move 13.} 1. e4 c6 2. c4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. cxd5 Nf6 5. Qa4+ Nbd7 6. Nc3 g6 7. Bc4 Bg7 8. d3 a6 ({My preference is} 8... O-O {completing the development of the kingside.}) 9. Nf3 O-O 10. Qa3 b6 11. O-O Bb7 12. Re1 Re8 13. Qb4 {The idea of this move is to transfer the queen to h4 after Bb3.} ({Another common move is} 13. Bd2 {In this case, however, Black does not face any problems -} b5 14. Bb3 Nb6 {It's clear that Black will comfortably regain the pawn.} 15. Ne4 {At this point, my preference is} Nfxd5 ({A high-profile game saw} 15... Bxd5 16. Ba5 Bxb3 17. Qxb3 Nxe4 18. dxe4 Qb8 $11 {with equality. 1/2 (37) -1/2 (37) Zherebukh, Y (2590) -Eljanov, P (2697) Khanty-Mansiysk 2011 CBM 145 [5.Qa4 - 13. Bd2]}) 16. d4 ({A thematic idea for Black can be seen in the line} 16. Ba5 b4 $1 {Remember this pawn sacrifice!} 17. Bxb4 Nxb4 18. Qxb4 a5 19. Qa3 a4 20. Bd1 (20. Bc4 Nxc4 21. dxc4 Qc7 $44) 20... e6 $13 {with a fantastic compensation for the pawn.}) 16... a5 17. Qc5 a4 18. Bxd5 Bxd5 19. Qxb5 Nc4 $15 {Black's piece activity and coordination provides more than enough compensation for the pawn.}) ({A dubious but tricky line is} 13. d6 $6 e6 14. Ng5 b5 15. Bb3 {[%csl Re1] Now, Black should make use of the fact that the e1-rook is unprotected. The best move is} h6 $1 ({After} 15... Rc8 16. Nge4 Ng4 17. Bf4 {White was better in 1-0 (35) Jovic, S (2240) -Laznicka,V (2675) Skopje 2018 CBM 187 Extra [5.Qa4 - 13.d6]}) 16. Nge4 (16. Nf3 Bxf3 17. gxf3 Nh5 $19) 16... Nd5 $1 {[%cal Gb5b4] This is the point. White has no defence against ...b5-b4. Black is already winning because after} 17. Nxd5 exd5 {[%cal Ge8e1] the knight will drop due to the pin.}) 13... b5 14. Bb3 Nb6 15. Qh4 Bxd5 $1 {The simplest solution. I prefer to keep the knight on b6 in order to answer d3-d4 with ... Nc4.} ({After} 15... Nbxd5 16. Ne5 {White has some annoying pressure.}) 16. Nxd5 {[%csl Bg7]} Nfxd5 {[%csl Bb6][%cal Bg7a1]} 17. d4 Nc4 $15 {This is the point.} 18. Bh6 f6 {[%csl Gc4,Gd5,Rf3][%cal Gd8d7,Ga8c8] Thematic move for the setups with ...g7-g6 against IQP. The idea is to restrict the f3-knight. Black is ready to follow with simple moves such as ...Qd7 and ...Rac8 with a better position.} *

