{The final lecture features the Fantasy Variation and all the other sidelines that White can try on moves 2 and 3. Besides providing in-depth analysis of the Fantasy Variation, I have also paid a serious attention to the system 1.e4 c6 2.Nf3 d5 3.exd5 cxd5 4.Ne5 which is a very serious option. In all the variations, I have tried to suggest easy-to-learn systems which are mainly based on strategic ideas. When I provide long variations, I mainly do it for illustration purposes. In most of the cases, you are not obliged to memorize them.}  *

